author: COMSOL
description: As an analyte band flows through a curved channel in an electroosmotically driven flow, dispersion of the band occurs due to gradients in the fluid velocity across the channel. These velocity gradients result from differences in the electric field acting at the walls within the curved channels. This example shows how to optimize the channel velocity to minimize the dispersion of the analyte.
